        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>[align=center]<a href="https://www.valvesoftware.com/publications/2008/GDC2008_CrossPlatformDevelopment.pdf" data-bbcode="true" rel="nofollow noopener">https://www.valvesoftware.com/publications/2008/GDC2008_CrossPlatformDevelopment.pdf</a></p>
<p>[align=left]I’m sure, at least once EP3 is released, valve is going to want to port it like they did with “still alive”…</p>
<p>It would make an interesting post-release community project. Just underclock a TriCore AMD thing down to 2.0ghz (~3.2Ghz without OOE/limited BP), get a 2900 GT (virtually identical to the Xenos) and downclock the RAM, get a gig of DDR2 in dual channel and try to keep the total memory footprint (vid+sys) under a half gig. No devkit required![/align]<br>
[/align]</p>
